<HL>
   Business Brief -- TSB Group PLC:
   Hill Samuel Unit Acquires
   Atlanta Capital Management
</HL>
<DATE>
04/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   U.TSB
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Hill Samuel Investment Management Group Ltd., a unit of
Britain's TSB Group PLC, said it has acquired closely held
Atlanta Capital Management Co. in the U.S. The purchase price
wasn't disclosed.
   The acquisition, which includes an agreement allowing its
senior executives to stay with the company, represents Hill
Samuel's second fund-management operation in the U.S. and
brings the unit's total funds under management to $10.2
billion.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Hill Samuel acquired a Minneapolis fund manager in 1986, a
company that currently has $7.6 billion of funds under
management. Atlanta Capital's managed funds total $1.6
billion currently. Hill Samuel's London operation also
controls an additional $1 billion in managed funds.
</TEXT>
